## 3. AUTHENTICATION

Two methods. For OIS: use **Basic Auth only**.

### 3.1 Basic Auth (API Key) `✓ Primary`

```
WHO    Building integrations for your own shop
HOW    HTTP Basic Auth — Base64(username:password) in Authorization header
WHERE  Credentials created at: https://my-shop.fourthwall.com/admin/dashboard/settings/for-developers
ROLE   SUPER ADMIN required to create credentials (see C10)
```

```bash
# cURL
curl -u "your_username:your_password" \
  https://api.fourthwall.com/open-api/v1.0/shops/current
```

```javascript
// JavaScript
const base64 = btoa("your_username:your_password");
fetch("https://api.fourthwall.com/open-api/v1.0/shops/current", {
  headers: { "Authorization": `Basic ${base64}` }
});
```

### 3.2 OAuth 2.0

```
WHO    Building apps for multiple shops (third-party integrations)
STATUS Invite-only — cannot self-register (see C2)
GUIDE  https://docs.fourthwall.com/guides/oauth
```

**OAuth scopes:**
```
shop_read · order_read · order_write · fulfillment_write
offer_read · offer_write · donation_read
giveaway_read · giveaway_write
memberships_read · memberships_write
promotions_read · promotions_write
thankyou_read · thankyou_write
webhook_read · webhook_write
```

### 3.3 Storefront Token (Storefront API only)

```
FORMAT    ptkn_xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx
PASSED AS ?storefront_token=YOUR_TOKEN  (query param)
LOCATION  Developer Settings → Storefront Token
SCOPE     Read-only public product data. Safe for client-side use.
```

