## 10. MERCH / PRODUCT SPECS `⚠️ C15 — Secondary`

### 10.1 Upload Requirements

```
Format      PNG preferred · JPEG accepted · No TIFF
            PNG required for any product needing transparency
Resolution  300 DPI recommended · 200 DPI floor for DTG garments
Upload size ~25 MB max per file
Transparency Full alpha only — no glows, semi-transparent edges, or fade effects
Bleed       Extend background past safe-area dotted line in editor
            Keep text/faces/logos well inside safe zone
Quality UI  Blue = pass · Yellow = fair · Red = too low
```

### 10.2 Product Dimensions

**Desk Mats** (Sublimation / Spoke):
```
Small  12×18″    → 3,600×5,400 px @ 300 DPI
Medium 12×22″    → 3,600×6,600 px
Large  15.5×31.5″ → 4,650×9,450 px
```

**Mouse Pads** (Sublimation / Printful):
```
Classic        8.7×7.1″  → 2,610×2,130 px
Gaming Medium  18×16″    → 5,400×4,800 px
```

**Other:**
```
Coasters     3.75×3.75″ → 1,125×1,125 px
Poster 10×10 → 3,000×3,000 px  (sRGB — inkjet, not CMYK)
Poster 18×24 → 5,400×7,200 px
Poster 24×36 → 7,200×10,800 px
```

**Sublimation:** Colors print darker/less saturated than screen. Push brightness and saturation 10–15% above target.

**Master canvas strategy:** `15,000×9,000 px @ 300 PPI · RGB · PSD or TIFF` — covers all OIS Fourthwall products except 24×36 poster.

**File naming:** `[Title]_[Product]_[Dimensions]_[ColorMode]_v[##].png`

