## 12. AI / LLM TOOLING `✓ Primary`

Fourthwall provides first-party AI tooling support. Three integration paths.

### 12.1 Documentation Files

| File | Size | Use |
|---|---|---|
| `https://docs.fourthwall.com/llms.txt` | ~45KB | Compact — hierarchical index with links. Start here to discover pages. |
| `https://docs.fourthwall.com/llms-full.txt` | ~592KB | Complete docs with full content. Use this as context for code generation. |

Follows the [llms.txt standard](https://llmstxt.org/).

**Recommended `.cursorrules` / `CLAUDE.md` / `copilot-instructions.md` snippet:**
```markdown
# Fourthwall Development
Fourthwall is an e-commerce platform for creators to sell merchandise, memberships, and digital products.
Documentation: https://docs.fourthwall.com/llms-full.txt

When working with Fourthwall APIs:
- Platform API: shop management (authentication, products, orders, inventory, webhooks)
- Storefront API: custom storefronts (cart, checkout, collections)
- Apps: OAuth apps with multi-shop support
- Security: HMAC signature verification for webhooks and embedded sections
```

### 12.2 MCP Server

Fourthwall hosts a native MCP server — AI tools can query docs directly instead of relying on web search.

```
URL   https://docs.fourthwall.com/mcp
```

**Claude Desktop:**
Settings → Connectors → Add custom connector → Name: `Fourthwall Docs` → URL: `https://docs.fourthwall.com/mcp`

**Claude Code (terminal):**
```bash
claude mcp add fourthwall-docs https://docs.fourthwall.com/mcp
```

**Cursor (`mcp.json`):**
```json
{
  "mcpServers": {
    "fourthwall-docs": {
      "url": "https://docs.fourthwall.com/mcp"
    }
  }
}
```

### 12.3 Context7

Also available via Context7 MCP server.
```
Project ID   /llmstxt/fourthwall_llms-full_txt
Setup        https://github.com/upstash/context7
```

